issue.title: Unit / Functional Tests for Initial Milestones
issue.body:
A basic suite of unit and function tests should be established to verify correctness and drive development towards our initial batch of milestones.

I don't think we need to strictly embrace TDD or pursue any particular coverage percentage, but I think having some tests in advance would give a clear idea of how the app should behave.

As for what exactly is a valuable testing target, I think that's up for discussion. I'd definitely like to see some coverage for anything interacting with live API data (with mocks) and anything that is used to determine when to send a notification.

issue.title: Player Names

milestone.title: API Integration
milestone.description:
We're currently working off of mocked data. We should set up live API access, whether that data is a real-time stream or just a batch of data for a day's games.

As we get a better idea of what these data sets look like, we can figure out how to mock them ourselves for testing purposes.

issue.body: We have mock data for player names when looking up by ID. This should be hooked up to an actual API, for live lookups.

issue.title: Interesting Event: Average Runs for Hitter vs. Pitcher

milestone.title: Interesting Engine
milestone.description:
We should have a few matchup statistics that can trigger an interesting notification.

We've already discussed a high number of runs for a given hitter vs. a pitcher. A few other metrics should be added, with thresholds for a notification. Whether this is sent out to users automatically or on an opt-in / opt-out model can be discussed as part of the UX.

issue.body:
If a hitter has a high number of average runs vs. a given pitcher per game, a notification should be triggered for subscribed users. The threshold should be high enough that the notifications aren't too frequent.

I think this is a good baseline to get the Interesting Engine up and running. :metal:

issue.title: Signup Form

milestone.title: Signup / Subscription Page
milestone.description:
We currently have a dummy signup / landing page. We should be able to perform a full signup, and send the user's phone number / email / whatever back to the API, in order to subscribe them to interesting events.

Part of this will be design discussion, part of this will be UI / UX for presenting subscription options.

issue.body: The signup form should submit a user's phone number and / or email to the server, so that it can be persisted.
